<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>8 SPEED, 9 SPEED, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - REASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the gear shift lever housing secured in a vise, install the spade pin in the bore
                    of the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13018j5">Figure 195</hotlnk>). If previously removed, install the O-ring in the
                    tower groove.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13018j5" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13018j5" filename="../figg13/G13018J5.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 194. Install Spade Pin in Bore of Housing Tower</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the gear shift lever in the housing with the spade pin in the lever ball slot
                    and install the tension spring washer over the ball, dished-side up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13018j6">Figure 196</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13018j6" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13018j6" filename="../figg13/G13018J6.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 195. Install Tension Spring Washer Over Ball</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tension spring under the lugs in the housing,
                    <emph type="bold">seating one coil at a time</emph>
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13018j7">Figure 197</hotlnk>). Use of a spring driving tool is recommended.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13018j7" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13018j7" filename="../figg13/G13018J7.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 196. Install Tension Spring Under Lugs in Housing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise and install the rubber boot over the gear shift lever
                    and against the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13018j8">Figure 198</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13018j8" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13018j8" filename="../figg13/G13018J8.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 197. Install Rubber Boot Over Gear Shift Lever</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
